kernel_variant.question:
Let $\bigl(a_{n}\bigr)_{n\ge 1}$ be an arbitrary sequence of strictly positive real numbers and put  
\[
A_{n}=a_{1}+a_{2}+\dots +a_{n}\qquad(n\ge 1).
\]

a) (Knopp's inequality - optimal form)  
Prove that  
\[
\boxed{\;
   \displaystyle 
   \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{n}{A_{n}}\le 2\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{a_{n}}
  \;} \tag{K}
\]
and show that the numerical constant $2$ is best possible.

b) (Impossibility of equality)  
Show that if $\displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}1/a_{n}<\infty$, then the
inequality in (K) is always strict.  
(When $\sum 1/a_{n}=+\infty$ the right-hand side of (K) is infinite,
so equality is meaningless.)

c) (Redheffer refinement - sharp finite and infinite versions)  
For every positive integer $k$ prove  
\[
\boxed{\;
   \frac{(k+1)^{2}}{A_{k}}+\sum_{n=1}^{k-1}\frac{2n+1}{A_{n}}
               \le 4\sum_{n=1}^{k}\frac{1}{a_{n}}
  \;} \tag{R}
\]
and deduce the infinite counterpart  
\[
\boxed{\;
    \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{2n+1}{A_{n}}
           \le 4\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{a_{n}}
   \;} \tag{R_\infty}
\]
Finally, prove that $4$ is the best possible constant in both (R) and $(R_\infty)$.

\vspace{1ex}

